I'm running through the tests here - http://wiki.eclipse.org/Equinox_p2_tests using the AdminUI.

For the "Basic install, run and update" test after updating from M2 to the latest integration build for m3. I run into problems. Eclipse runs however I get an error dialog that pops up with the following error.

An error has occurred. See error log for more details.
org.eclipse.osgi.service.resolver.State.getDisabledInfos(Lorg/eclipse/osgi/service/resolver/BundleDescription;)[Lorg/eclipse/osgi/service/resolver/DisabledInfo;


config.ini looks ok except for osgi.bundles.extraData which contains all of the bundles installed for 3.4 M3.

The bundles.txt file contains both the old and new org.eclipse.osgi bundle but otherwise looks like it updated correctly.

(I'll save this install if anyone wants to see other files)

--

I've logged bug 208065 for the osgi.bundles.extraData issue.

The remaining issue for this bug is the duplicate org.eclipse.osgi bundles when updating.

The error dialog will only happen if we use the "Plug-in Registry" view in an SDK that beens updated between M2 and M3.

The remaining problem is that the old framework jar will be used instead of the new org.eclipse.osgi jar. It looks like the problem is in how we're updating config.ini and other associated issues in frameworkadmin.

This is not critical and also not safe for M3. Re-targetting for M4
Fix and regression tests added to HEAD.
